label.value: heart left ventricle end-systolic posterior wall index

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the heart left ventricle end-systolic posterior wall thickness is divided by the weight of the body, and the result presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: calculated heart left ventricle end-systolic internal diameter

definition.value: A measurement which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of the heart left ventricle end-systolic internal diameter.

label.value: heart left ventricle end-systolic diameter to body weight ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the heart left ventricle end-systolic internal diameter is divided by the weight of the body, and the result presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: calculated heart ventricle end-systolic septal wall thickness

definition.value: A measurement which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of the heart ventricle end-systolic septal wall thickness.

label.value: heart ventricle end-systolic septal wall index

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the heart ventricle end-systolic septal wall thickness is divided by the weight of the body, and the result presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

definition.value: Peak velocity of late atrial diastolic trans-mitral flow (A).
E' wave velocity is the peak velocity of early mitral annular diastolic motion.
A' wave velocity (A') is the peak velocity of late (atrial) diastolic mitral annular motion.
The amount of enzymatic activity of α-N-acetylgalactosaminidase (NAGA) in a specified sample of blood.

label.value: blood NH2-terminal pro-B-type natriuretic peptide level

value.value: This is a measurement of the amount of N-terminal (NT)-pro hormone BNP (NPPB) in a specified volume of blood.

label.value: plasma NH2-terminal pro-B-type natriuretic peptide level

definition.value: This is a measurement of the amount of N-terminal (NT)-pro hormone BNP (NPPB) in a specified volume of plasma.
A measurement which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of the amount of aldosterone in a specified sample of plasma.

label.value: plasma aldosterone level to plasma renin activity ratio

definition.value: A measurement which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of cardiac output.
A calculated measurement in which the cardiac output is divided by the weight of the body, and the result presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.
A measurement which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of cardiac stroke volume.
A calculated measurement in which the cardiac stroke volume is divided by the weight of the body, and the result presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: calculated left ventricular end-systolic blood pressure

definition.value: A measurement which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of the left ventricular end-systolic blood pressure.

value.value: Effective arterial elastance (Ea), defined as the ratio of left ventricular end-systolic pressure (Pes) to stroke volume (SV), provides a convenient, useful method to assess arterial load.
Defined as the work performed by the left or right ventricle to eject the stroke volume into the aorta or pulmonary artery, respectively.
Defined as the work performed by the left ventricle to eject the stroke volume into the aorta.

label.value: preload recruitable left ventricle stroke work

value.value: Preload recruitable stroke work (PRSW) is determined by the linear regression of stroke work with the end-diastolic volume. The slope of the PRSW relationship is a highly linear index of myocardial contractility that is insensitive to preload and afterload.

label.value: maximum rate of positive change in left ventricular blood pressure to left ventricular end-diastolic volume ratio

definition.value: A calculated measurement in which the maximum rate of positive change in left ventricular blood pressure is divided by the left ventricular end-diastolic volume, and the result presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: calculated heart left ventricle end-diastolic posterior wall thickness

definition.value: A measurement which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of the end-diastolic heart left ventricle posterior wall thickness.

label.value: heart left ventricle end-diastolic posterior wall index

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the heart left ventricle end-diastolic posterior wall thickness is divided by the weight of the body, and the result presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: calculated heart left ventricle end-diastolic anterior wall thickness

definition.value: A measurement which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of the heart left ventricle end-diastolic anterior wall thickness.

label.value: heart left ventricle end-diastolic anterior wall index

definition.value: A calculated measurement in which the heart left ventricle end-diastolic anterior wall thickness is divided by the weight of the body, and the result presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: calculated heart ventricle end-diastolic septal wall thickness

definition.value: A measurement which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of the heart ventricle end-diastolic septal wall thickness.

label.value: heart ventricle end-diastolic septal wall index

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the heart ventricle end-diastolic septal wall thickness is divided by the weight of the body, and the result presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

definition.value: Measurement of the amount of a ketone body, 3-hydroxybutyrate, in a specified sample of urine.

value.value: This is a measurement of the amount of a ketone body, acetoacetate, in a specified sample of urine. Acetoacetate is the conjugate base of acetoacetic acid, a physiologically relevant ketone body.

definition.value: The amount of glycated albumin in a specified volume of blood. Glycation is the result of a sugar molecule, such as fructose or glucose, bonding to a protein or lipid molecule without the controlling action of an enzyme.

label.value: blood glycated albumin level to blood albumin level ratio

definition.value: A calculated measurement in which the amount of glycated albumin in a specified sample of blood is divided by the amount of total albumin in that same sample, and the result presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

value.value: A measurement which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of the amount of hemoglobin, or a derivative of hemoglobin, in a specified sample of blood.

definition.value: A measurement which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of the amount of glycated albumin in a specified sample of blood.

value.value: Renal medullary blood flow (MBF) is the volume of blood delivered to or exiting from the renal medulla per unit time.

The amount of vasopressin in a specified volume of blood. Vasopressin belongs to family of cyclic nonapeptide hormones found in most mammals. Synthesised in the hypothalamus and stored in the post-pituitary, vasopressins play a key role in homeostasis, particularly in regulating the body's water content. Together with the similar neuropeptide oxytocin, they are believed to influence social cognition and behaviour

definition.value: The amount of vasopressin in a specified volume of plasma. Vasopressin belongs to family of cyclic nonapeptide hormones found in most mammals. Synthesised in the hypothalamus and stored in the post-pituitary, vasopressins play a key role in homeostasis, particularly in regulating the body's water content. Together with the similar neuropeptide oxytocin, they are believed to influence social cognition and behaviour.

The amount of vasopressin in a specified volume of serum. Vasopressin belongs to family of cyclic nonapeptide hormones found in most mammals. Synthesised in the hypothalamus and stored in the post-pituitary, vasopressins play a key role in homeostasis, particularly in regulating the body's water content. Together with the similar neuropeptide oxytocin, they are believed to influence social cognition and behaviour.
Measurement of the amount of phosphorus, measured as inorganic phosphate eliminated from the body in the urine per unit time.
The amount of urea excreted into the urine within a specified period of time.

value.value: Left ventricle end-diastolic elastance (Eed) is the estimate of the slope of the line Ped = Eed(Ved-V0), which is based on linear regression of points determined by iterative calculation of the LV end-diastolic pressure-volume relationship.

Left ventricle end-systolic elastance (Ees) is the estimate of the slope of the line Pes = Ees(Ves-V0), which is based on linear regression of points determined by iterative calculation of the LV end-systolic pressure-volume relationship.

definition.value: A measurement which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of components of the periodic tightening and loosening of the muscles of a ventricle of the heart.

label.value: heart left ventricle diastolic volume-axis intercept

value.value: Left ventricle diastolic volume-axis intercept (V0) is determined by the line Ped = Eed(Ved-V0), which is based on linear regression of points determined by iterative calculation of the LV end-diastolic pressure-volume relationship. Ped = end-diastolic pressure, Ved = end-diastolic volume, V0  theoretical volume when no pressure is generated, Eed (end-diastolic elastance, stiffness) is the slope of the EDPVR (LV end-diastolic pressurevolume relationship).

label.value: heart left ventricle systolic volume-axis intercept

value.value: Left ventricle systolic volume-axis intercept (V0) is determined by the line Pes = Ees(Ves-V0), which is based on linear regression of points determined by iterative calculation of the LV end-diastolic pressurevolume relationship. Pes = end-systolic pressure, Ves = end-systolic volume, V0  theoretical volume when no pressure is generated, Ees (index of LV systolic function, contractility) is the slope of the ESPVR (LV end-systolic pressurevolume relationship).

definition.value: A measurement of the volume of blood in ventricle immediately before a contraction which has been normalized or adjusted by a mathematical process or computation. .

value.value: A measurement of the volume of blood in a ventricle at the end of a contraction which has been normalized or adjusted by a mathematical process or computation.

definition.value: The amount of adrenomedullin in a specified sample of kidney tissue.
The amount of adrenomedullin in a specified sample of medullary kidney tissue.
